<b>What are the signs of possession?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">There are certain signs of possession which include:</span>

<b>Strange behaviors</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Â The host will start acting strangely in a way they never did before. For instance, they may start smoking or speaking jargon. Their overall behavior is totally off the road.</span>

<b>Nightmares</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Demons are stronger at night, so the possessed individual may experience horrible night terrors. They make suddenly wake up at night and start doing strange things.</span>

<b>Uncomfortable with prayer</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">This is one of the most obvious signs a person is possessed. They physically become sick at the presence of a priest or exorcists especially when praying.</span>

<b>Stages of demonic possession</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Generally, there are 3 stages of possession. They are the:</span>

<b>Manifestation stage</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In this stage, the demon comes in and introduces itself to the targeted individual. This may occur as seeing the ghost of a dead relative. At this stage, the demon is waiting to be approved.</span>

<b>Oppression stage</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">At this stage, the demon shows its true identity and launches attacks on its host. The attack could be mental, physical, or psychical.</span>

<b>Complete passion</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">This is the last and most dangerous stage. The demon completely takes over its host. At this point, the affected person has no power or faith left.</span>

<b>Getting rid of possession</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Getting a certified exorcist or shamanic healer is the best step to take. They will help you get rid of the demons and restore normality back to your life.</span>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"0";}}